               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Tāʾrīkh-i Khān Jahān Lūdī va makhzan al-Afghānī by Khvājah Niʿmat Allāh ibn Khvājah Ḥabīb Allāh al-Hiravī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115922 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064911 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2005005467" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_610-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>History of the Afghān or Pathān nation claiming descent from a lost tribe of Israel after the <persName key="viaf_202148389276110710871" role="subject">Patriarch Yaʿqūb or Jacob</persName>, with particular reference to Afghan ruling dynasties in India until the restoration of Timurid rule under the Timurid (Mughal) Emperor Bābur, written by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657181.0x000001 viaf_35539655" role="aut">Khvājah Niʿmat Allāh ibn Khvājah Ḥabīb Allāh al-Hiravī</persName> under the patronage of <persName key="viaf_29062577" role="pat">Pīrā Khān Lūdī entitled Khān Jahān</persName> (d. 1040/1631), the protégé of Emperor Jahāngīr (d. 1037/1627), but executed under Emperor Shāh Jahān I (d. 1076/1666). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Work on the history commenced in 1018/1609 and completed during the patron’s participation in the second campaign to conquer the Deccan kingdom of Aḥmadnagar, 20 Z̲ī al-Ḥijjah 1020/23 February 1612, at qaṣbah Malkāpūr in the district of Birār. </p>
                        <p>The work is slightly defective at the beginning, having lost a few leaves from the preface. 
</p>
                        <p>The work comprises of a muqaddimah, eight sections termed bāb, and concluding khātimah. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 247v): completed on the morning of Thursday, 15 Rabīʿ al-S̲ānī in RY 37 [probably of Emperor Shāh ʿĀlam], (1210)/29 October 1795. </p>
                        <p>Distinct nastaʿlīq, occasionally blurred and smudged. 
</p>
                        <p>Original covers lost. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios rebound in IOL red half leather binding (IOL stamp dated 26 Nov 1974), with leaves remounted in new margins and conserved with tissue overlay throughout. Stains, tears, wormholes. 
</p>
                     </note>
